Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy applies to the Peep Plans mobile application (hereby referred to as the “Application”), developed by Aled Bound (hereby referred to as the “Service Provider”) as a commercial application. The Application is provided “AS IS”.

What information does the Application obtain and how is it used?

The Application allows users to create and manage Personal Emergency Evacuation Plans (PEEPs), together with associated information such as building details, contacts, notes, attachments, and other planning-related data.

Basic features of the Application may store information locally on your device.

Subscription plans include cloud synchronisation as part of the service. When you subscribe, relevant Application data is securely stored and synchronised using cloud services to enable features such as multi-device access, backups, and data recovery. By subscribing and confirming the relevant prompts within the Application, you authorise the storage and synchronisation of this information.

The Application may also use Apple’s iCloud services where appropriate to synchronise your data between your Apple devices. Data stored in iCloud is subject to Apple’s privacy and security practices.

The Service Provider does not use your information for advertising, profiling, or marketing purposes and does not sell your personal information.

How is your information stored?

Depending on the features you use:

* Data may be stored locally on your device.
* Subscription data is securely synchronised using cloud services operated on behalf of the Service Provider.
* Where supported, data may also be synchronised via your personal iCloud account.

Cloud synchronisation remains active while your subscription is active. If your subscription ends, new cloud synchronisation will cease, although previously stored data may be retained where necessary to manage your account, comply with legal obligations, or allow restoration if you resubscribe, subject to the Service Provider’s data retention policies.

Does the Application collect precise real-time location information?

No.

The Application does not collect or transmit your device’s precise location unless you explicitly use a feature that requires location access and grant permission.

Do third parties see and/or have access to information obtained by the Application?

The Service Provider does not share your information with advertisers, marketing companies, or data brokers.

Your information is processed by trusted service providers only where necessary to deliver the Application’s functionality, including secure cloud storage and Apple iCloud synchronisation.

Where your local Fire and Rescue Service uses the companion High Rise Evacuation application, information that you have authorised may be made available to that organisation to support emergency planning and operational response. This sharing occurs only where you have provided the necessary authorisation through the Application.

If you choose to export or share information using features provided by the Application, you are responsible for determining who receives that information.

Children

The Application is not intended for children under the age of 13 and is not designed to knowingly collect personal information from children.

The Service Provider does not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children. If you believe that a child has provided personal information through the Application, please contact 63.vim_visor@icloud.com so that appropriate action can be taken.

Where required by applicable law, users must be at least 16 years of age, or have the consent of a parent or legal guardian, before providing personal information.

Security

The Service Provider takes reasonable administrative, technical, and organisational measures to protect your information.

Information stored remotely is transmitted using encrypted connections and protected using appropriate authentication and industry-standard security practices. Access to synchronised information is restricted to authorised users and authorised organisations where sharing has been approved by the user.

Although every reasonable effort is made to protect your information, no method of electronic storage or transmission over the Internet can be guaranteed to be completely secure.

